::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:07.150 --> 00:00:09.860
Even if the world won't accept her...

3
00:00:09.860 --> 00:00:12.700
she's a part of it now.

4
00:00:13.080 --> 00:00:15.910
She is undeniably human.

5
00:00:16.790 --> 00:00:18.500
It was a success.

6
00:00:19.290 --> 00:00:21.380
I am certain of it now.

7
00:00:21.380 --> 00:00:26.010
This is a huge step toward world peace.

8
00:00:26.340 --> 00:00:31.050
Dr. Vegapunk, the director of MADS,
the Laboratory for Peace.

9
00:00:32.570 --> 00:00:34.550
US, US

10
00:00:35.170 --> 00:00:40.410
US, ALL OF US

11
00:00:44.040 --> 00:00:46.840
The end of the dream, the end of the sea

12
00:00:46.840 --> 00:00:48.820
We all have different places we want to go We all have different places we want to go WE ALL HAVE DIFFERENT PLACES WE WANT TO GO

13
00:00:46.860 --> 00:00:49.600
We all have different places we want to go

14
00:00:49.600 --> 00:00:52.380
But to start we've got to show what we're made of

15
00:00:52.380 --> 00:00:56.730
We'll be legends, we're gonna take the world by storm

16
00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:00.320
Sparks are flying, NO LIMITS! This is where it starts

17
00:01:00.320 --> 00:01:01.600
ONE PIECE!!

18
00:01:01.960 --> 00:01:04.580
VORONOI START VORONOI END ALL OF US, I've got a question for you ALL OF US, I've got a question for you

19
00:01:04.580 --> 00:01:08.170
Have you let the world and all its burdens bring your dreams down?

20
00:01:09.810 --> 00:01:16.370
Every cell in me is getting restless - They're about to blow, oh, it's just too much Every cell in me is getting restless - They're about to blow, oh, it's just too much

21
00:01:16.480 --> 00:01:23.100
Still we try, ALL OF US have our own paths we cling to

22
00:01:23.100 --> 00:01:25.690
ALL OF US, I've got something to tell you ALL OF US, I've got something to tell you

23
00:01:24.690 --> 00:01:26.220
ALL OF US, I've got something to tell you If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall

24
00:01:25.750 --> 00:01:29.270
If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall

25
00:01:25.810 --> 00:01:29.120
If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall

26
00:01:30.960 --> 00:01:33.650
Random clues suddenly fit together

27
00:01:33.650 --> 00:01:37.580
Starting to make sense, oh, what's going on?

28
00:01:37.580 --> 00:01:44.050
Threads of time weaving into an intricate tapestry

29
00:01:44.140 --> 00:01:49.750
We can't stop the world from turning, it's changing along with every one of-

30
00:01:50.350 --> 00:01:52.320
US, US

31
00:01:52.940 --> 00:01:57.430
US, ALL OF US

32
00:02:06.730 --> 00:02:09.400
There's nowhere to run now.

33
00:02:06.770 --> 00:02:11.940
<b>The Weight of Memory</b>

34
00:02:09.400 --> 00:02:11.940
All that's left to do is take out Vegapunk.

35
00:02:12.490 --> 00:02:15.780
Now, how should we drag him out?

36
00:02:16.160 --> 00:02:18.790
That Frontier Dome is a real pain.

37
00:02:18.790 --> 00:02:20.830
It sure packs a wallop.

38
00:02:21.620 --> 00:02:25.080
You're not going to listen
to the Marines, Lucci?

39
00:02:26.500 --> 00:02:29.340
I don't acknowledge Straw Hat as an Emperor.

40
00:02:31.130 --> 00:02:32.970
Goodness me...

41
00:02:37.680 --> 00:02:40.970
Agents are rushing to block all sailing routes.

42
00:02:40.970 --> 00:02:44.440
Every ship on the island
is in danger of being captured...

43
00:02:45.060 --> 00:02:49.400
but unfortunately, Vegaforce-01 can only
fly within the island's atmosphere...

44
00:02:50.150 --> 00:02:52.280
It's an effective strategy.

45
00:02:54.990 --> 00:02:57.870
We've gotta avenge Atlas, don't we?!

46
00:02:57.870 --> 00:03:01.830
Our only objective now is to escape.

47
00:03:01.830 --> 00:03:03.250
Having said that...

48
00:03:03.250 --> 00:03:05.160
it looks like a fight is inevitable.

49
00:03:05.540 --> 00:03:06.540
What's going on?

50
00:03:06.540 --> 00:03:08.130
Is it something fun?

51
00:03:08.130 --> 00:03:10.170
I'm rarin' to go!

52
00:03:10.170 --> 00:03:14.130
Well, I don't think anyone can get up here,

53
00:03:14.510 --> 00:03:17.890
so we don't actually need to
go out of our way to fight them...

54
00:03:17.890 --> 00:03:18.930
Huh?!

55
00:03:19.470 --> 00:03:20.760
Lilith!

56
00:03:20.760 --> 00:03:23.220
Don't rush into battle recklessly.

57
00:03:23.220 --> 00:03:24.310
Huh?!

58
00:03:24.310 --> 00:03:26.190
Hey, Shaka! What's your problem?!

59
00:03:26.190 --> 00:03:30.650
Why can't we fight these whippersnappers?
They're the ones trying to kill us!

60
00:03:32.780 --> 00:03:36.570
Our goal is not retaliation.
We need to help the stella escape.

61
00:03:36.570 --> 00:03:39.820
We can't do that if we don't take 'em out!

62
00:03:39.820 --> 00:03:42.540
Alright, let's all calm down...

63
00:03:42.540 --> 00:03:44.450
We are his satellites.

64
00:03:44.450 --> 00:03:48.250
We must ensure his safety,
even at our own peril.

65
00:03:48.620 --> 00:03:50.710
That's our priority.

66
00:03:52.460 --> 00:03:54.670
We can't have you running wild.

67
00:03:57.630 --> 00:04:00.890
You're a goody two-shoes, as always.

68
00:04:00.890 --> 00:04:03.600
I hate your guts.

69
00:04:03.600 --> 00:04:04.970
I'll survive.

70
00:04:08.480 --> 00:04:11.440
Eureka! I just came up with
a new, innovative technology!

71
00:04:11.440 --> 00:04:12.770
But!

72
00:04:15.030 --> 00:04:18.240
I ain't got enough time
or people to do the research!

73
00:04:18.240 --> 00:04:20.990
I'd even take help from a cat at this point!

74
00:04:22.070 --> 00:04:23.370
Oh, Joshu!

75
00:04:23.740 --> 00:04:26.080
Much obliged for your assistance!

76
00:04:26.080 --> 00:04:28.330
Oh, Sentomaru...

77
00:04:28.330 --> 00:04:31.130
Look what happened when you took my side...

78
00:04:31.130 --> 00:04:31.960
I'm sorry!

79
00:04:32.540 --> 00:04:33.800
What should we do?

80
00:04:33.800 --> 00:04:37.170
We do have one more ally on the island...

81
00:04:37.170 --> 00:04:38.510
Hold your horses!

82
00:04:38.510 --> 00:04:44.140
Taking our side will mean getting exposed
and chased down by the government!

83
00:04:44.140 --> 00:04:45.600
Yes, you're right...

84
00:04:45.600 --> 00:04:47.890
Anyway, that's the long and short of it...

85
00:04:47.890 --> 00:04:48.480
– What?
– Huh?

86
00:04:48.980 --> 00:04:51.190
Now I'm stuck in the lab.

87
00:04:51.190 --> 00:04:54.820
Now... hold on just a minute!
That ain't a smart idea!

88
00:04:54.820 --> 00:04:56.440
Put that down!

89
00:04:56.440 --> 00:05:00.490
I'm in a spot of trouble,
so could you help me out-quasar?

90
00:05:00.490 --> 00:05:02.910
– What a shameless cry for help!
– What a shameless cry for help!

91
00:05:02.910 --> 00:05:04.530
Of course.

92
00:05:04.530 --> 00:05:06.240
I've been waiting for your order.

93
00:05:08.750 --> 00:05:10.620
We're getting help, folks!

94
00:05:10.620 --> 00:05:13.130
All it took was my order!

95
00:05:13.750 --> 00:05:16.170
Seems like the best option we have...

96
00:05:16.170 --> 00:05:17.380
Yeah!

97
00:05:17.380 --> 00:05:22.090
Once CP0 is under control,
getting away should be a piece of cake!

98
00:05:22.510 --> 00:05:24.970
Stella! Hitch a ride with the Straw Hats!

99
00:05:25.300 --> 00:05:26.470
Alright!

100
00:05:26.470 --> 00:05:29.980
I'll use Vegaforce-01 to
take the ship to the port, then!

101
00:05:29.980 --> 00:05:31.600
That's good. Let's hurry up.

102
00:05:31.600 --> 00:05:33.980
Don't boss us around!

103
00:05:33.980 --> 00:05:36.440
That really pisses me off!

104
00:05:36.980 --> 00:05:39.400
Now, let's start escaping.

105
00:05:39.400 --> 00:05:41.110
Don't ignore me!

106
00:05:44.070 --> 00:05:45.830
All right, folks.

107
00:05:46.160 --> 00:05:50.080
Everything's all set, so please
let me aboard your ship-quasar.

108
00:05:50.080 --> 00:05:51.460
Yeah! Let's go!

109
00:05:51.910 --> 00:05:54.540
Oh, wait. There are seven
of us that need a ride.

110
00:05:54.880 --> 00:05:55.790
Seven?

111
00:05:55.790 --> 00:05:58.550
You mean all the Vegapunks are coming with?!

112
00:05:58.550 --> 00:06:02.300
Going on a voyage with seven
of the world's best scientists!

113
00:06:02.300 --> 00:06:03.510
Super!

114
00:06:03.510 --> 00:06:06.640
Huh...? Sounds like a pain in the ass...

115
00:06:06.640 --> 00:06:08.640
It's becoming more and more of a burden!

116
00:06:08.640 --> 00:06:11.140
Seven Vegapunks...

117
00:06:11.140 --> 00:06:13.140
Does that mean...

118
00:06:13.140 --> 00:06:16.150
Lilith will be coming with?!

119
00:06:16.150 --> 00:06:18.400
Then you're totally welcome!

120
00:06:18.400 --> 00:06:21.400
Lilith my love...!

121
00:06:24.990 --> 00:06:28.450
Vegapunk!

122
00:06:28.450 --> 00:06:31.160
How dare you swarm me with bugs?!

123
00:06:31.160 --> 00:06:32.080
Oh no!

124
00:06:32.080 --> 00:06:35.580
Now she's just mad about the bugs!

125
00:06:35.580 --> 00:06:39.880
Hey! I promised that old man
I'd get him out of here!

126
00:06:39.880 --> 00:06:42.090
Don't kick his ass, Bonney!

127
00:06:42.090 --> 00:06:44.300
I'll never forgive him!

128
00:06:46.260 --> 00:06:47.800
What's that?

129
00:06:51.100 --> 00:06:55.480
Labophase defense system:
Frontier Dome deactivating.

130
00:06:55.900 --> 00:06:59.940
Labophase defense system:
Frontier Dome deactivating.

131
00:07:00.480 --> 00:07:01.530
Why?

132
00:07:01.530 --> 00:07:02.650
Who did it?

133
00:07:02.650 --> 00:07:03.950
For what reason?

134
00:07:03.950 --> 00:07:04.950
Pythagoras!

135
00:07:04.950 --> 00:07:06.570
What's going on?!

136
00:07:06.570 --> 00:07:07.530
I don't know!

137
00:07:07.530 --> 00:07:10.580
The Frontier Dome's
interception system is down!

138
00:07:11.080 --> 00:07:15.370
There's nothing stopping the enemy
from reaching the Labophase now!

139
00:07:16.120 --> 00:07:18.130
Is there somebody in the control room?!

140
00:07:18.630 --> 00:07:19.840
Let me check!

141
00:07:21.920 --> 00:07:22.840
Negative!

142
00:07:22.840 --> 00:07:25.590
There's nobody in the control room!

143
00:07:26.680 --> 00:07:29.760
Then... who did it?!

144
00:07:34.180 --> 00:07:37.520
Frontier Dome deactivated.

145
00:07:38.150 --> 00:07:39.610
What's going on...?

146
00:07:39.610 --> 00:07:40.770
Lucci!

147
00:07:40.770 --> 00:07:42.530
The barrier is deactivated!

148
00:07:42.530 --> 00:07:43.820
Now's our chance!

149
00:07:43.820 --> 00:07:45.030
Wait.

150
00:07:45.030 --> 00:07:46.150
It could be a trap.

151
00:07:47.360 --> 00:07:50.120
If so, this is a golden opportunity!

152
00:07:50.120 --> 00:07:52.450
We don't wanna miss it!

153
00:07:52.450 --> 00:07:54.450
This is too convenient for us.

154
00:07:54.950 --> 00:07:56.830
Don't you think it's strange?

155
00:07:56.830 --> 00:07:59.670
We'll know if it's a trap 
or not once we get close to it!

156
00:07:59.670 --> 00:08:02.380
If we just stay here,
we can't fulfill our mission!

157
00:08:02.380 --> 00:08:03.960
I'm going!

158
00:08:04.590 --> 00:08:06.550
Follow me!

159
00:08:07.010 --> 00:08:08.180
Guess we're going.

160
00:08:17.690 --> 00:08:20.190
See, look! No light show!

161
00:08:20.190 --> 00:08:22.440
It's off, just like I thought!

162
00:08:22.440 --> 00:08:24.150
It wasn't a trap!

163
00:08:24.150 --> 00:08:28.110
This is it, this is it! This is our chance!

164
00:08:28.490 --> 00:08:30.820
Your life is at stake now,

165
00:08:30.820 --> 00:08:35.080
but I guess you're down
on your luck, Vegapunk.

166
00:08:37.910 --> 00:08:40.420
Is that the Straw Hats' ship?

167
00:08:42.130 --> 00:08:44.170
I get it now.

168
00:08:44.170 --> 00:08:46.920
This is why we didn't see
their ship down there.

169
00:08:46.920 --> 00:08:48.550
There's a spiffy robot, too!

170
00:08:49.010 --> 00:08:50.800
Let's destroy it.

171
00:08:51.800 --> 00:08:53.220
In a jiffy!

172
00:08:58.140 --> 00:08:59.770
Dishes are done.

173
00:08:59.770 --> 00:09:03.270
Maybe I should clean the deck while I'm at it...

174
00:09:04.150 --> 00:09:07.990
I wonder what that alarm earlier was about.

175
00:09:22.710 --> 00:09:24.420
Tempest Kick...

176
00:09:25.130 --> 00:09:26.840
Sky Slicer!

177
00:09:46.190 --> 00:09:47.270
What happened?!

178
00:09:47.270 --> 00:09:50.320
What was that?! An explosion?!

179
00:09:53.450 --> 00:09:57.450
Who disturbed my nap?

180
00:09:57.450 --> 00:09:59.290
Roronoa!

181
00:10:01.250 --> 00:10:02.460
Shaka!

182
00:10:02.460 --> 00:10:07.290
The Frontier Dome has been reactivated,
but CP0 already got through.

183
00:10:07.800 --> 00:10:08.920
Dammit...

184
00:10:08.920 --> 00:10:10.010
It's too late!

185
00:10:10.010 --> 00:10:12.630
They're going for the Straw Hats' ship.

186
00:10:12.630 --> 00:10:13.760
Indeed.

187
00:10:14.090 --> 00:10:17.390
Whoever was watching
the ship is fighting back!

188
00:10:19.430 --> 00:10:23.890
We have to back them up
or we'll lose our means of escape!

189
00:10:29.190 --> 00:10:32.150
See? We gotta tussle after all!

190
00:10:32.150 --> 00:10:34.910
Let's ambush CP0!

191
00:10:34.910 --> 00:10:35.910
Calm down.

192
00:10:35.910 --> 00:10:38.030
I don't want you to get out of control.

193
00:10:42.500 --> 00:10:43.910
Dang it, Bonney!

194
00:10:44.500 --> 00:10:45.790
Where did she go?

195
00:10:47.750 --> 00:10:50.630
Hey! Guys!

196
00:10:52.510 --> 00:10:54.840
Luffy! Chopper!

197
00:10:55.340 --> 00:10:56.800
Jinbe!

198
00:11:02.270 --> 00:11:05.190
Hey! There's a bunch of cool stuff here!

199
00:11:05.190 --> 00:11:06.270
Like a huge robot!

200
00:11:06.270 --> 00:11:09.820
Let's grab the Vegapunks
and get off this island already!

201
00:11:10.190 --> 00:11:12.530
What?! We're leaving already?

202
00:11:12.900 --> 00:11:15.030
But we just got here!

203
00:11:15.030 --> 00:11:16.910
Let's stay a little more!

204
00:11:16.910 --> 00:11:19.280
We'd love to stay, too...

205
00:11:19.280 --> 00:11:21.870
but this is a government island!

206
00:11:22.240 --> 00:11:25.080
You saw Rob Lucci, didn't you?!

207
00:11:28.670 --> 00:11:30.750
Something's going on outside.

208
00:11:31.130 --> 00:11:35.510
Cipher Pol will be here any second,
so we can't waste any time.

209
00:11:35.510 --> 00:11:37.510
But...

210
00:11:39.010 --> 00:11:40.800
Have you seen Bonney?

211
00:11:40.800 --> 00:11:43.140
She's a pirate girl with long hair.

212
00:11:43.520 --> 00:11:47.350
She's the one who was
with you down at the robot?

213
00:11:47.690 --> 00:11:51.020
She's trying to kill Vegapunk.

214
00:11:51.020 --> 00:11:52.900
– What?!
– What?!

215
00:11:52.900 --> 00:11:54.400
Why?

216
00:11:54.400 --> 00:11:56.530
Speaking of, where is Vegapunk?

217
00:11:56.530 --> 00:11:58.820
Oh, yeah, I haven't seen him.

218
00:12:03.330 --> 00:12:05.120
Vegapunk!

219
00:12:08.500 --> 00:12:10.790
Why you...!

220
00:12:11.170 --> 00:12:12.590
Vegapunk!

221
00:12:17.470 --> 00:12:19.180
Stop running!

222
00:12:19.800 --> 00:12:21.550
Stop it, Bonney!

223
00:12:21.550 --> 00:12:23.390
I'm in a hurry!

224
00:12:25.140 --> 00:12:27.270
But I still want to talk to you!

225
00:12:27.270 --> 00:12:29.020
Listen to me first!

226
00:12:29.480 --> 00:12:30.270
Shut up!

227
00:12:31.940 --> 00:12:33.440
Stop it, Bonney!

228
00:12:36.320 --> 00:12:38.490
Wait, you asshole!

229
00:12:39.280 --> 00:12:41.280
All I wanna hear...

230
00:12:41.280 --> 00:12:44.240
is whether you can
change my father back or not!

231
00:12:44.240 --> 00:12:46.950
I just want a yes or no answer!

232
00:12:46.950 --> 00:12:48.710
I can't...

233
00:12:49.580 --> 00:12:51.330
do that.

234
00:12:51.330 --> 00:12:52.420
I'm sorry.

235
00:12:52.420 --> 00:12:54.170
Then...

236
00:13:05.010 --> 00:13:06.850
I have no choice but to kill you!

237
00:13:06.850 --> 00:13:09.020
Wait! There's a reason!

238
00:13:14.690 --> 00:13:15.440
Damn!

239
00:13:15.440 --> 00:13:18.860
<b>Red Port

At the Foot
of the Red Line</b>

240
00:13:34.340 --> 00:13:35.750
What was that?!

241
00:14:18.420 --> 00:14:19.760
What just fell?!

242
00:14:23.930 --> 00:14:26.300
B-Bartholomew Kuma?!

243
00:14:26.300 --> 00:14:27.550
What?

244
00:14:27.550 --> 00:14:28.930
Where did he come from?

245
00:14:28.930 --> 00:14:32.680
I heard he recently escaped
from the Land of the Gods!

246
00:14:33.310 --> 00:14:35.270
Why is he here?!

247
00:14:35.270 --> 00:14:37.980
It's the Celestial Dragons'
invincible slave, Kuma...

248
00:14:37.980 --> 00:14:39.650
Why is he here?!

249
00:14:58.500 --> 00:15:01.880
Northeast region, near the bondola landing!

250
00:15:02.260 --> 00:15:06.260
The former Warlord
Bartholomew Kuma has appeared!

251
00:15:08.140 --> 00:15:10.390
All Marines, report to the area!

252
00:15:19.360 --> 00:15:23.280
All citizens, evacuate the area immediately!

253
00:15:23.280 --> 00:15:24.190
Warning!

254
00:15:24.820 --> 00:15:29.450
This individual is no longer human
and is a slave kept by the Celestial Dragons!

255
00:15:29.830 --> 00:15:31.700
His current programming is unknown!

256
00:15:31.700 --> 00:15:33.330
This situation is dangerous!

257
00:15:33.330 --> 00:15:36.040
Evacuate immediately!

258
00:15:48.220 --> 00:15:50.850
It hurts!

259
00:15:50.850 --> 00:15:53.890
I think I broke a bone...

260
00:15:55.480 --> 00:15:57.100
B-Bonney...

261
00:15:58.810 --> 00:16:00.020
Oh no!

262
00:16:00.770 --> 00:16:02.230
Are you okay?!

263
00:16:02.230 --> 00:16:03.820
I have to get the medical team!

264
00:16:05.820 --> 00:16:08.280
Bonney got hurt!

265
00:16:13.490 --> 00:16:17.660
Distorted Future!

266
00:16:18.870 --> 00:16:20.710
Vegapunk!

267
00:16:20.710 --> 00:16:22.090
Huh?!

268
00:16:27.340 --> 00:16:28.930
I was fooled!

269
00:16:32.220 --> 00:16:33.890
Stop running!

270
00:16:33.890 --> 00:16:35.060
Don't, Bonney!

271
00:16:35.060 --> 00:16:36.520
Even if you kill me...

272
00:16:37.390 --> 00:16:39.390
Age Skewer!

273
00:17:01.580 --> 00:17:03.130
Damn...

274
00:17:03.500 --> 00:17:06.800
These shiny things are the years I lost, right?!

275
00:17:07.210 --> 00:17:09.220
How could you turn me into a little kid?!

276
00:17:09.590 --> 00:17:13.010
Give me back my golden years!

277
00:17:16.850 --> 00:17:18.140
Don't worry.

278
00:17:18.730 --> 00:17:22.940
My powers don't affect
living things permanently.

279
00:17:23.440 --> 00:17:27.070
You said there was a reason!

280
00:17:29.400 --> 00:17:30.780
So spit it out.

281
00:17:31.660 --> 00:17:34.370
Why did you kill my father?!

282
00:17:36.660 --> 00:17:39.500
But, Bonney, if I tell you...

283
00:17:40.000 --> 00:17:43.630
it'll only... hurt you.

284
00:17:43.630 --> 00:17:44.460
So...

285
00:17:48.510 --> 00:17:52.550
I made a promise with Kuma...

286
00:17:56.260 --> 00:17:59.730
<b>Red Port</b>

287
00:17:56.850 --> 00:18:00.020
Kuma started climbing the Red Line!

288
00:18:00.020 --> 00:18:02.940
There's no way he can climb it! This is crazy!

289
00:18:10.860 --> 00:18:16.160
I promised him that I would
never tell you the reason...

290
00:18:24.330 --> 00:18:28.250
You had a reason to kill my father,
but you can't say it?!

291
00:18:28.630 --> 00:18:30.090
Do you think I'm stupid?!

292
00:18:30.460 --> 00:18:32.050
Screw you!

293
00:18:32.050 --> 00:18:35.050
I don't think you're stupid!

294
00:18:35.640 --> 00:18:37.260
Please just forget about it!

295
00:18:39.600 --> 00:18:42.600
The decision to give up his humanity...

296
00:18:42.600 --> 00:18:44.480
was his own,

297
00:18:44.480 --> 00:18:46.650
and no one else's!

298
00:18:46.650 --> 00:18:48.360
You're lying!

299
00:18:48.860 --> 00:18:52.610
There's no way he'd choose
to die and leave me behind!

300
00:18:53.150 --> 00:18:54.950
You killed him!

301
00:18:54.950 --> 00:18:57.320
It was hard for me, too!

302
00:18:57.320 --> 00:18:59.830
I don't even want to remember!

303
00:19:15.840 --> 00:19:18.850
Kuma is a good man!

304
00:19:18.850 --> 00:19:21.600
I'm proud to call him my friend!

305
00:19:21.600 --> 00:19:24.560
I'm very fond of him!

306
00:19:25.060 --> 00:19:26.770
So please understand, Bonney!

307
00:19:27.270 --> 00:19:28.560
I can't say anything!

308
00:19:29.150 --> 00:19:30.360
No, tell me!

309
00:19:34.320 --> 00:19:38.530
How can I be convinced by
such a self-serving excuse?

310
00:19:40.280 --> 00:19:41.790
You're abusing me!

311
00:19:42.160 --> 00:19:43.870
Please stop!

312
00:19:47.750 --> 00:19:49.290
What?!

313
00:19:51.710 --> 00:19:53.000
That's nothing!

314
00:19:53.000 --> 00:19:54.170
Wait, Bonney!

315
00:19:54.170 --> 00:19:57.430
It has nothing to do with Kuma!

316
00:19:57.430 --> 00:19:58.840
Looks like it does.

317
00:20:02.510 --> 00:20:04.310
Oiled Shock.

318
00:20:21.120 --> 00:20:23.080
No, Bonney!

319
00:20:42.640 --> 00:20:43.680
Bonney...

320
00:20:52.560 --> 00:20:54.360
Memories?

321
00:20:54.360 --> 00:20:55.940
That's right.

322
00:20:55.940 --> 00:20:59.820
Some scholar in the West Blue said...

323
00:21:00.200 --> 00:21:04.790
people lose 21 grams
at the moment of death...

324
00:21:05.660 --> 00:21:09.790
Which means that's the weight of their soul.

325
00:21:10.750 --> 00:21:13.460
It's very interesting!

326
00:21:13.460 --> 00:21:16.460
The soul exists.

327
00:21:16.460 --> 00:21:18.420
That's for sure!

328
00:21:21.510 --> 00:21:23.640
I don't know what you're talking about.

329
00:21:26.010 --> 00:21:28.100
Don't you think it's similar...

330
00:21:29.520 --> 00:21:31.310
to your power?

331
00:21:35.650 --> 00:21:40.070
It gives a person's intangible
pain a physical form...

332
00:21:40.070 --> 00:21:42.280
and passes it on to others.

333
00:21:46.990 --> 00:21:51.330
It transfers the electrical signals of
peripheral nerves without wires.

334
00:21:57.090 --> 00:21:59.670
How about mental images?

335
00:22:00.010 --> 00:22:01.630
Mental images?

336
00:22:01.630 --> 00:22:07.470
That's right! Images and memories
are also signals from nerve cells!

337
00:22:09.720 --> 00:22:11.020
What is their mass?

338
00:22:11.020 --> 00:22:13.020
What is their volume?

339
00:22:13.350 --> 00:22:16.860
That's what I want to know!

340
00:22:17.570 --> 00:22:20.690
Are you asking me to pull my memories
out and show them to you?!

341
00:22:20.690 --> 00:22:22.780
Do you want me to embarrass myself?

342
00:22:22.780 --> 00:22:24.280
I'm begging you!

343
00:22:24.280 --> 00:22:25.990
It's for science!

344
00:22:25.990 --> 00:22:28.030
I won't show them to anyone else!

345
00:22:28.030 --> 00:22:29.450
I promise.

346
00:22:29.450 --> 00:22:30.700
Forget it.

347
00:22:30.700 --> 00:22:33.290
I can't trust a request from you!

348
00:22:35.290 --> 00:22:36.330
Come on,

349
00:22:36.330 --> 00:22:38.630
please...!

350
00:22:38.630 --> 00:22:41.300
Listen! Don't touch it, Bonney!

351
00:22:41.300 --> 00:22:43.260
That right there is pain!

352
00:22:44.090 --> 00:22:47.640
You know how Kuma's power works!

353
00:22:47.640 --> 00:22:52.180
That pain is strong enough to kill someone!

354
00:22:53.310 --> 00:22:54.690
No...

355
00:22:54.690 --> 00:22:55.730
It's not.

356
00:22:57.360 --> 00:22:58.820
Dad...

357
00:23:04.110 --> 00:23:07.120
<b>Red Port</b>

358
00:23:08.580 --> 00:23:10.080
Shoot Kuma down!

359
00:23:10.080 --> 00:23:12.250
Do not allow him to reach Mary Geoise!

360
00:23:22.090 --> 00:23:23.300
Keep firing!

361
00:23:28.180 --> 00:23:29.680
He's falling!

362
00:23:34.600 --> 00:23:35.940
Hurry!

363
00:23:35.940 --> 00:23:37.060
Surround him!

364
00:23:43.110 --> 00:23:44.950
Evacuate this area!

365
00:23:44.950 --> 00:23:46.150
– Run!
– Run!

366
00:23:46.150 --> 00:23:48.200
You'll get hurt!

367
00:23:56.750 --> 00:23:59.460
This isn't pain.

368
00:24:02.300 --> 00:24:05.630
I'm very familiar with my father's power.

369
00:24:05.630 --> 00:24:07.260
Finish him off!

370
00:24:09.800 --> 00:24:10.890
R-Retreat!

371
00:24:16.020 --> 00:24:17.230
These are...

372
00:24:20.060 --> 00:24:22.070
his memories, aren't they?

373
00:24:51.430 --> 00:24:54.810
<b>Lab</b>

374
00:24:51.720 --> 00:24:54.810
What?! Rob Lucci got up here?!

375
00:24:54.810 --> 00:24:56.020
My apologies.

376
00:24:56.020 --> 00:24:57.520
The system malfunctioned.

377
00:24:57.520 --> 00:24:59.640
Good thing Zoro and Brook stayed behind!

378
00:24:59.640 --> 00:25:01.730
There's no way they'll lose!

379
00:25:01.730 --> 00:25:03.110
It's two against three.

380
00:25:03.110 --> 00:25:05.030
So it depends how they fight.

381
00:25:06.480 --> 00:25:08.110
No, look closer.

382
00:25:08.610 --> 00:25:10.570
The odds are much worse.

383
00:25:11.820 --> 00:25:13.160
What?!

384
00:25:13.160 --> 00:25:15.540
The seraphim are here, too!

385
00:25:15.540 --> 00:25:17.250
It's two against seven.

386
00:25:17.250 --> 00:25:18.960
And they're all strong.

387
00:25:19.580 --> 00:25:22.460
We didn't even give them any orders...

388
00:25:22.460 --> 00:25:24.340
We can't make them go back!

389
00:25:25.630 --> 00:25:27.840
The dome has already been closed.

390
00:25:29.800 --> 00:25:31.300
Dammit!

391
00:25:31.300 --> 00:25:35.060
They called in the seraphim
while the defense system was down!

392
00:25:35.060 --> 00:25:38.810
No, I don't think CP0 would want them here.

393
00:25:40.440 --> 00:25:42.730
Depending on the circumstances...

394
00:25:43.100 --> 00:25:47.110
the seraphim have limited
decision-making capabilities.

395
00:25:49.070 --> 00:25:52.570
So they figured they had a chance
while the barrier was down.

396
00:25:52.570 --> 00:25:55.200
CP0 probably didn't expect this.

397
00:25:55.200 --> 00:25:57.370
Perhaps we can catch them off guard.

398
00:25:58.830 --> 00:26:00.410
